# JQuery Hashchange
***
This plugin was inspired and forked from [Andrey Popelo](https://github.com/apopelo/jquery-hashchange).
Thanks to Andrey popelo.

## Features:
* Calls `onSet()` function when the `window.loction.hash` sets.
* Calls `onRemove()` function when the `window.loction.hash` removed. 
* Support the dynamic hashes i.e. fragment values which are generated dynamically.
  example: 
           #user/123 - To view the details of user with id 123.
           #user/123/edit - To edit the user details with id 123
* Passing values of dynamic hashes to the `onSet` and `onRemove` functions.

## Example:
* Here the `onSet` and `onRemove` functions are called when the hash "#company" sets or remove respectively. 
`$(window).hashchange(
                {
                    hash: "#company",
                    onSet: function() {
                        $("#compList").show();
                    },
                    onRemove:function(){
                        $("#compList").hide();
                    }
                }
);`

* Setting hash functions (`onSet` and `onRemove`) for dynamic hashes. Getting the values in `onSet` and `onRemove` functions.
For example the url is http://abc.com/company.html#company/123 . Then the 123 dynamic value pass to `onSet` and `onRemove` as array.

`{
    hash: "#company/%s",
    regex: true,
    onSet: function(arr) {
              var companyId=arr[0];
              $("#compDetail").show();
           },
    onRemove:function(arr){
              var companyId=arr[0];
              $("#compDetail").hide();
           }
 }` 
 
To get complete reference see index.html in demo directory.
